sentences: Sven-Bertil Gunnar Evert Taube (born 24 November 1934) is a Swedish singer and actor.
Taube graduated in 1954 from the Cherry Lawn School in Darien, Connecticut.
Taube has been married four times, and has four children, born in 1960, 1965, 1979, and 1994.

He belongs to an untitled branch of the Baltic German noble Taube family, introduced at the Swedish House of Nobility in 1668 as noble family No. 734.
Taube released his first album in 1954; it included a cover of one of his father's songs.
